---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: '8 Best SEO.AI Alternatives in 2026 (Ranked and Reviewed)',
  description: 'Looking for SEO.AI alternatives? We tested 8 tools that automate content. From $19/mo to full done-for-you SEO at $99/mo with local SEO included.',
  canonical: 'https://thestacc.com/alternatives/seo-ai/',
  ogImage: '/og/alternatives-seo-ai.webp',
  schemaData: [
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Alternatives", "item": "https://thestacc.com/alternatives/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "SEO.AI Alternatives", "item": "https://thestacc.com/alternatives/seo-ai/" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "ItemList",
      "name": "8 Best SEO.AI Alternatives in 2026",
      "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending",
      "numberOfItems": 8,
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "theStacc", "url": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Scalenut" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Surfer SEO" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Koala AI" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Outranking" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Content at Scale" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Machined AI" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "Frase" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the best SEO.AI alternative in 2026?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For local service businesses and SMBs, theStacc is the best alternative — it writes, optimizes, and publishes 30 articles/month for $99, plus handles Google Business Profile posts and social media. For teams on a tight budget, Scalenut ($30/mo annual) offers the most features per dollar." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is there a free SEO.AI alternative?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Koala AI has a free tier with 5,000 words. Machined AI offers a free plan with limited clusters. MarketMuse has a free plan with 10–35 queries. None match SEO.AI's full autopilot for free, but they're functional starting points." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is SEO.AI worth $149/month?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "If every feature worked as advertised, maybe. But broken keyword research, irrelevant suggestions, and misleading SEO scores undermine the value. At $149/month you should expect reliability — and SEO.AI doesn't consistently deliver it. theStacc offers a more complete package at $99/month." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Which SEO.AI alternative is cheapest?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Koala AI starts at $9/month (annual). Outranking starts at $19/month. Scalenut is $30/month on annual billing. theStacc is $99/month but includes writing, publishing, local SEO, and social media." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can I switch from SEO.AI to theStacc?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. theStacc replaces SEO.AI's content automation, adds local SEO and social media, and costs $50/month less. Sign up for $1 (3-day trial) and theStacc starts publishing optimized articles to your WordPress, Webflow, or Ghost site within days." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does SEO.AI publish to any CMS?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — SEO.AI supports WordPress, Webflow, Wix, Squarespace, Shopify, and Magento. This is one area where SEO.AI has broader CMS support than most competitors, including theStacc (which supports WordPress, Webflow, Ghost, and Custom Webhook)." }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout seo={seo}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <a href="/alternatives/" class="hero-pill">
      <span class="pill-dot"></span>
      <span>Alternatives roundup · Q2 2026 update</span>
      <span class="pill-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
    <h1 class="h-display">8 Best <span class="accent">SEO.AI Alternatives</span> in 2026</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">SEO.AI had the right idea — full autopilot content publishing. But broken keyword research, misleading quality scores, and no local SEO channel left teams looking elsewhere. We tested 8 SEO.AI alternatives that fix the problems. Winner: theStacc.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Try the #1 alternative — $1 <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
      <a href="#ranked-list" class="btn btn-secondary">See all 8 alternatives</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>8 alternatives</strong> tested across content automation</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>$1 trial</strong> · No contract</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>Last updated <strong>Q2 2026</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TRUST -->
  <section class="trust-section">
    <div class="trust-head">
      <p class="trust-label">Used by teams that left SEO.AI</p>
      <div class="trust-rating">
        <span class="trust-rating-text"><strong>4.9</strong> from <strong>127 reviews</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-logos">
      <div class="trust-logo"><img src="/customer-logos/replydaddy.webp" alt="ReplyDaddy" loading="lazy"/><span>ReplyDaddy</span></div>
      <div class="trust-logo"><img src="/customer-logos/noobbooklm.webp" alt="NoobBookLM" loading="lazy"/><span>NoobBookLM</span></div>
      <div class="trust-logo"><img src="/customer-logos/chartmath.webp" alt="ChartMath" loading="lazy"/><span>ChartMath</span></div>
      <div class="trust-logo logo-only"><img src="/customer-logos/heaven-designs.webp" alt="Heaven Designs" loading="lazy"/></div>
      <div class="trust-logo logo-only"><img src="/customer-logos/heaven-green-energy.webp" alt="Heaven Green Energy" loading="lazy"/></div>
      <div class="trust-logo logo-only"><img src="/customer-logos/qbits.webp" alt="Qbits Energy" loading="lazy"/></div>
      <div class="trust-logo logo-only"><img src="/customer-logos/quickestimate.webp" alt="QuickEstimate" loading="lazy"/></div>
      <div class="trust-logo logo-only"><img src="/customer-logos/intello.webp" alt="Intello" loading="lazy"/></div>
      <div class="trust-logo"><img src="/customer-logos/suryantra-energy.webp" alt="Suryantra Energy" loading="lazy"/><span>Suryantra Energy</span></div>
      <div class="trust-logo logo-only"><img src="/customer-logos/suncart.svg" alt="Suncart" loading="lazy"/></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY PEOPLE LEAVE SEO.AI -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Why teams leave SEO.AI</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">SEO.AI promised autopilot. <span class="accent">The reality didn't match.</span></h2>
      <p>SEO.AI's concept is solid — automated content planning, writing, and CMS publishing. But after testing it and reading user reviews, six recurring problems surface that break the hands-off promise.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">The SEO.AI gap</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Six reasons teams switch away.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Documented across user reviews as of Q2 2026.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>High entry price relative to competitors</h4>
              <p>$149/month monthly ($89 annual) is steep when tools like Scalenut ($30/mo annual) and Koala AI ($9/mo annual) offer similar automation at a fraction of the cost.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Keyword research surfaces irrelevant topics</h4>
              <p>Users consistently report that the keyword gap tool recommends keywords with no connection to their niche. If your keyword foundation is wrong, every article built on top of it is wasted effort.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Non-functional features</h4>
              <p>Multiple users report the Keyword Gap feature is completely broken. For a $149/month tool, broken core features are a dealbreaker — not a minor annoyance.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Misleading quality scores</h4>
              <p>Keyword-stuffed content scores "excellent" in SEO.AI's grader. That means the score measures keyword density, not actual content quality — a dangerous signal to optimize toward.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Blog content only — no local SEO, no social</h4>
              <p>If you run a local business, you need Google Business Profile posts and social scheduling too. SEO.AI covers one channel. You still need separate tools for everything else.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">06</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Multi-site pricing jumps to $299/month</h4>
              <p>Single Site is $149/month. Multi Site is $299/month. Agencies managing multiple clients face significant costs compared to alternatives with more reasonable multi-site pricing.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What teams want instead</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Autopilot that actually works — across all channels.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Not broken features. Not misleading scores. Finished, published work.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>30 articles written AND published for $99 — not $149</h4>
              <p>theStacc does the same autopilot job SEO.AI promises at $50/month less. WordPress, Webflow, Ghost, and custom webhooks supported.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Google Business Profile posts included</h4>
              <p>SEO.AI has zero local SEO features. theStacc adds GBP automation at $49/mo — blog SEO and local SEO on one platform.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>92% average SEO score — no misleading metrics</h4>
              <p>Our scores reflect actual optimization quality, not keyword stuffing. What you see is what Google sees.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FEATURED #1 ALTERNATIVE -->
  <section class="modules-bento" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="modules-tabs-header">
      <span class="label-pill">#1 alternative</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">The winner: <span class="accent">theStacc.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">SEO.AI automates blog content. theStacc automates blog SEO, local SEO, and social media — at $50/month less, with no broken features.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-grid">
      <a class="bento-card bento-feature" href="/">
        <div class="bento-num">01</div>
        <div class="bento-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">theStacc — the #1 SEO.AI alternative for 2026</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">Writes, SEO-optimizes, and <span class="accent">publishes 30 articles</span> directly to your site. $99/mo.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">theStacc does everything SEO.AI promises — and adds the channels SEO.AI doesn't cover. 30 articles per month, written and published to your CMS. Google Business Profile posts. Social media content. Reliable keyword research. Accurate SEO scoring. All at $99/month — $50/month less than SEO.AI's entry price.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 fully written articles per month, published to your CMS</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Google Business Profile posts included ($49/mo add-on)</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Social media posts across Instagram, LinkedIn, X, Facebook</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>$1 trial · No contract · 24-hour setup</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bento-mock">
          <div class="bento-mock-bar">
            <div class="bento-mock-meta">THESTACC · #1 PICK · $99/MO</div>
            <span class="bento-mock-pulse"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="bento-mock-title">30 articles/mo, written + scored + published</div>
          <div class="bento-mock-tags">
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">$99/mo</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag">SEO 92% avg</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">Auto-publish</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bento-cta">Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST 2-8 -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Alternatives #2–8</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">7 more <span class="accent">SEO.AI alternatives</span> worth knowing.</h2>
      <p>Each one solves at least one of SEO.AI's core problems. Pick based on which problem hits hardest for your team.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · $30/MO ANNUAL ($59 MONTHLY)</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Scalenut — best budget automation alternative</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Most features per dollar on this list. GEO optimization is genuinely forward-looking.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">Scalenut gives you AI writing, content optimization, GEO features, WordPress publishing, and AI humanization at $30/month on annual billing. That's the best feature-to-price ratio on this list. The 7-day free trial doesn't require a credit card. Content quality is formulaic and needs editing, but the scope is unmatched at this price.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Best value per feature on this list</h4><p>$30/month annual covers AI writing, optimization, GEO, and WordPress publishing.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>GEO optimization for AI search visibility</h4><p>Optimize for ChatGPT, Google AIO, and Perplexity — forward-looking feature.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>7-day free trial, no credit card</h4><p>Evaluate the full platform before committing.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: content is formulaic and needs heavy editing</h4><p>Cancellation complaints mirror SEO.AI's issues. Ranking drops reported on unedited output.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $99/MO ANNUAL ($119 MONTHLY)</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Surfer SEO — best if quality was your problem with SEO.AI</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The most trusted content optimization scoring in the industry. 500-factor analysis.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">If SEO.AI's misleading quality scores drove you away, Surfer is the antidote. The 500-factor Content Editor is the most granular and trusted optimization tool available — agencies worldwide use it as the standard. You still write and publish yourself, but the scoring guidance is the most reliable on the market.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Most trusted optimization scoring</h4><p>500-factor analysis — leagues ahead of SEO.AI's misleading scores.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Industry standard for content teams</h4><p>Used by agencies and in-house SEO teams as the quality benchmark.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>WordPress integration built in</h4><p>Optimize and push to WordPress without copy-pasting.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: manual control tool — you still write and publish</h4><p>No autopilot. No local SEO. Over-optimization risk if you chase scores blindly.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · $9/MO ANNUAL ($15 MONTHLY)</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Koala AI — cheapest bulk article generation alternative</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">$9/month with SERP analysis baked in. Built for volume over polish.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">Koala AI generates long-form SEO articles with real-time SERP analysis built into the generation process — not as a separate step. WordPress auto-publish with Gutenberg blocks. KoalaLinks handles automatic internal linking. Deep Research mode on the higher plans uses GPT-5 and Claude. If price was your problem with SEO.AI, this is the budget fix.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Cheapest entry with SEO features</h4><p>$9/month annual. 5,000 word free tier to evaluate.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>SERP analysis baked into every article</h4><p>Not a separate step — it's embedded in the generation workflow.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>WordPress + automatic internal linking</h4><p>KoalaLinks handles links on publish.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: 100% AI detection rates and documented Google penalties</h4><p>Output sounds robotic at scale. Support is slow (5+ day response times).</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · $19/MO · STARTER PLAN</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Outranking — best affordable factual AI writing alternative</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">50+ source analysis per article. Lowest entry price on this list.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">Outranking processes 50+ sources per article to keep output factually grounded — a meaningful differentiator when SEO.AI's content quality was the issue. Automatic internal linking and WordPress publishing are included at $19/month. The UI is rough and reliability has been questioned, but the accuracy emphasis is real.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Lowest entry price on this list</h4><p>$19/month for 4–5 documents.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>50+ source analysis per article</h4><p>Factual grounding SEO.AI doesn't prioritize.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Automatic internal linking + WordPress publishing</h4><p>Both included at base price.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: clunky UI and questionable platform reliability</h4><p>Trustpilot 3.0/5. AI credits burn faster than expected.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#6 · $249/MO ($208 ANNUAL) — REBRANDED AS BRANDWELL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Content at Scale — best for long-form autopilot at volume</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">2,000–5,000 word articles with WordPress and Shopify auto-publish.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">Content at Scale (now BrandWell) generates the longest articles on this list and markets itself as producing "undetectable AI content." WordPress and Shopify auto-publishing are included. If you want autopilot like SEO.AI but with longer, more detailed articles, this is the closest match — at $249/month, it's more expensive than SEO.AI itself.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Longest articles of any tool on this list</h4><p>2,000–5,000 words per article with built-in AI detection checking.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>WordPress and Shopify auto-publish</h4><p>Broader CMS coverage than most competitors.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Brand voice customization</h4><p>Train it on your style before generating.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: more expensive than SEO.AI ($249 vs $149) and AI detection claims are overstated</h4><p>Rebrand from Content at Scale to BrandWell caused user confusion.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#7 · $49/MO + API COSTS · STARTER PLAN</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Machined AI — best for topic cluster generation</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Give it a seed keyword. It builds a complete hub-and-spoke content cluster.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">Machined AI takes a different approach than SEO.AI — instead of individual articles, it generates entire topic clusters. One seed keyword becomes a hub page plus supporting articles with automatic internal links. WordPress and Webflow auto-publishing are included. The BYOK model means you pay OpenAI API costs on top of the subscription, so total cost is unpredictable.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Only tool that builds complete topic clusters automatically</h4><p>Hub-and-spoke architecture with automatic internal linking between articles.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>WordPress and Webflow publishing</h4><p>More CMS options than most cluster tools.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Free plan to test the approach</h4><p>Limited clusters available at no cost.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: BYOK means unpredictable total costs</h4><p>Content needs editing and human review. Small user base.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" style="margin-top: 40px;">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#8 · $49/MO ($39 ANNUAL) · STARTER PLAN</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Frase — best if SEO.AI's broken research drove you away</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The most reliable SERP research and best brief builder in the category.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">Frase is the direct fix if SEO.AI's irrelevant keyword suggestions and broken research features were your reason for leaving. The brief builder pulls headings, word counts, topics, and PAA questions from top-ranking pages — reliably, every time. Dual SEO + GEO scoring covers both traditional search and AI-generated answers. 7-day free trial, no credit card.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
